WEBVTT

1
00:00:37.538 --> 00:00:38.830
What the fuck is that?

2
00:00:40.082 --> 00:00:41.500
Oh. my God.

3
00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:17.702
Okay. Marines. Thirty seconds.

4
00:01:17.703 --> 00:01:19.830
[radio chatter in various languages]

5
00:03:04.476 --> 00:03:05.768
[Elena]
The nav system's saying

6
00:03:05.769 --> 00:03:09.273
the SEEKER's 0.3 kilometers
south-southeast.

7
00:03:10.607 --> 00:03:11.817
But that makes no sense.

8
00:03:12.651 --> 00:03:15.695
We turned northwest
at the ridge about a kilometer back there.

9
00:03:15.696 --> 00:03:17.321
We would have driven right past it.

10
00:03:17.322 --> 00:03:18.739
It's inertial navigation.

11
00:03:18.740 --> 00:03:19.783
It's not just guessing.

12
00:03:20.492 --> 00:03:21.742
- [sighs]
- [Walt] Besides.

13
00:03:21.743 --> 00:03:24.413
we went only about 0.6 kilometers.

14
00:03:36.216 --> 00:03:38.051
There. There she is.

15
00:03:50.189 --> 00:03:52.106
Bet she never thought she'd see us again.

16
00:03:52.107 --> 00:03:54.484
She is a robot. She doesn't have...

17
00:03:55.569 --> 00:03:56.778
Okay.

18
00:04:01.074 --> 00:04:03.910
[Kelly] Walt.
while you're getting the sample out.

19
00:04:03.911 --> 00:04:06.787
let's see if we can figure out what
damaged the SEEKER's electronics.

20
00:04:06.788 --> 00:04:08.956
[Elena] What the hell is that stuff?

21
00:04:08.957 --> 00:04:11.793
I don't know.
It almost looks like a tholin.

22
00:04:12.461 --> 00:04:15.255
But tholins shouldn't harm our SEEKERs.

23
00:04:16.423 --> 00:04:22.887
Well... [sighs] ...something about them
or this environment must be different.

24
00:04:22.888 --> 00:04:26.767
[sighs] Whatever it is.
it reacted with the insulation.

25
00:04:27.351 --> 00:04:30.102
It's no wonder
these things kept shorting out.

26
00:04:30.103 --> 00:04:31.479
Forget the tholins.

27
00:04:31.480 --> 00:04:33.357
This is what we came for.

28
00:04:41.657 --> 00:04:45.244
Crazy to think that those might hold
the greatest discovery in human history.

29
00:04:46.411 --> 00:04:47.621
[chuckles] No pressure.

30
00:04:48.539 --> 00:04:52.041
[Walt] Let's get this into the mobile lab
so we can run a full analysis.

31
00:04:52.042 --> 00:04:53.293
see what's what.

32
00:05:25.909 --> 00:05:27.536
That's good.

33
00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:59.318
Well. as my mom used to say.
it's out of our hands now.

34
00:06:00.569 --> 00:06:01.570
Yeah.

35
00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:09.870
While we're waiting.
maybe we should check another sample.

36
00:06:11.997 --> 00:06:15.166
Let's fire up
the scanning electron microscope too.

37
00:06:15.167 --> 00:06:16.834
We can run a test from the underside

38
00:06:16.835 --> 00:06:19.045
where it would've been protected
from radiation.

39
00:06:19.046 --> 00:06:21.547
[Walt] Right. We can run it through
to calibrate the bio...

40
00:06:21.548 --> 00:06:24.133
[Oleg] <i>Titan crew. come in.
This is</i> Sojourner<i>.</i>

41
00:06:24.134 --> 00:06:26.052
Uh. boss. <i>Sojourner</i> calling.

42
00:06:26.053 --> 00:06:27.804
- Yeah. Put him through.
- Go ahead.

43
00:06:28.472 --> 00:06:29.598
New boss. Sorry.

44
00:06:37.439 --> 00:06:38.898
<i>Sojourner</i>. Away-1.

45
00:06:38.899 --> 00:06:40.107
What's up?

46
00:06:40.108 --> 00:06:42.193
[Oleg] <i>We still haven't heard from Mars.</i>

47
00:06:42.194 --> 00:06:45.446
<i>The latest message was supposed
to come in over an hour ago.</i>

48
00:06:45.447 --> 00:06:49.158
Keep at it. I know they were gonna send us
the new ascent trajectory for our launch.

49
00:06:49.159 --> 00:06:51.160
We need that to get back home.

50
00:06:51.161 --> 00:06:53.080
[Oleg] <i>Copy. I'll keep trying.</i>

51
00:06:53.664 --> 00:06:57.543
<i>Something must be up. They've never been
this late with their check-in before.</i>

52
00:07:09.763 --> 00:07:11.765
- [alarm blaring]
- [distant clamoring]

53
00:07:12.975 --> 00:07:15.519
[panting]

54
00:07:17.020 --> 00:07:19.647
Hey. Someone saw ships landing.
Is it the M-6?

55
00:07:19.648 --> 00:07:22.316
Yes. it's true. M-6 ships have landed.

56
00:07:22.317 --> 00:07:23.860
- Come on.
- [gasps]

57
00:07:23.861 --> 00:07:25.571
- [Lily] Oh. shit.
- [Alex] This way.

58
00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:29.116
- [people shouting]
- [peacekeeper] Listen!

59
00:07:30.826 --> 00:07:34.036
Listen! Listen! That is
all the information I have right now.

60
00:07:34.037 --> 00:07:36.789
As soon as I know more.
you will know more. All right?

61
00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:40.668
I need you to stay calm.
and we will figure this out.

62
00:07:40.669 --> 00:07:43.629
- That's all I have.
- [Miles] <i>Attention. Happy Valley.</i>

63
00:07:43.630 --> 00:07:45.173
<i>This is Miles Dale.</i>

64
00:07:45.174 --> 00:07:49.427
<i>Ten minutes ago. the M-6 landed
military ships surrounding our base.</i>

65
00:07:49.428 --> 00:07:50.596
<i>Our home.</i>

66
00:07:51.096 --> 00:07:53.764
<i>Fighting has broken out
in the north and south.</i>

67
00:07:53.765 --> 00:07:56.184
<i>Any members of the Happy Valley Corps.</i>

68
00:07:56.185 --> 00:07:59.020
<i>please report
to your designated rally points.</i>

69
00:07:59.021 --> 00:08:00.396
<i>And any other volunteers...</i>

70
00:08:00.397 --> 00:08:03.317
<i>We're going to need everyone
who can help fight off this attack.</i>

71
00:08:03.942 --> 00:08:07.029
<i>Stay strong.
and remember this is our home.</i>

72
00:08:07.738 --> 00:08:10.573
- Okay. We gotta focus. all right?
- Where do we go?

73
00:08:10.574 --> 00:08:12.366
- I don't want to split up.
- Yeah. neither do I.

74
00:08:12.367 --> 00:08:14.620
Okay. Screw it. I'm staying with you.

75
00:08:15.621 --> 00:08:17.705
[gasping. clamoring]

76
00:08:17.706 --> 00:08:20.458
[peacekeeper] Okay. just keep calm.
Please just keep calm.

77
00:08:20.459 --> 00:08:21.918
J-Just keep calm. please.

78
00:08:21.919 --> 00:08:23.420
Can you just keep calm? Please.

79
00:08:24.713 --> 00:08:28.175
All right. we've lost main power.
We are on emergency backup.

80
00:08:28.759 --> 00:08:31.052
They must have taken over the reactors.

81
00:08:31.053 --> 00:08:32.637
Oh. my God. Ollie.

82
00:08:32.638 --> 00:08:34.221
Ollie's still out there.

83
00:08:34.222 --> 00:08:36.642
[chattering]

84
00:08:37.643 --> 00:08:39.436
[Marine 1] Hey. Dick.
did you bring the diapers?

85
00:08:41.772 --> 00:08:43.190
[Marine 2] Come on. Hernandez.

86
00:08:44.399 --> 00:08:46.651
Singh. get on the horn to the eltee.

87
00:08:46.652 --> 00:08:48.402
Let him know we've secured
the reactor complex

88
00:08:48.403 --> 00:08:50.655
and have reconfigured
for level-two interior combat.

89
00:08:50.656 --> 00:08:52.907
We've commenced base
power supply shutdown.

90
00:08:52.908 --> 00:08:54.200
[Singh] Yes. Sergeant.

91
00:08:54.201 --> 00:08:55.785
Rocky. Rocky One.

92
00:08:55.786 --> 00:08:57.538
- We have secured the reactor...
- Hey.

93
00:08:58.330 --> 00:08:59.414
You okay?

94
00:09:02.376 --> 00:09:04.878
Just... keep going
over it in my head. you know.

95
00:09:06.255 --> 00:09:07.923
One moment he was there. and then...

96
00:09:08.590 --> 00:09:09.842
[sighs]

97
00:09:11.552 --> 00:09:12.553
Yeah.

98
00:09:17.182 --> 00:09:18.725
He saved my life. goddamn it.

99
00:09:21.311 --> 00:09:22.687
Now he's dead.

100
00:09:22.688 --> 00:09:24.314
And these fuckers did that.

101
00:09:26.900 --> 00:09:28.276
[Fleming] Hey. let's can the chatter.

102
00:09:28.277 --> 00:09:30.319
- Let's get to work.
- Aye. aye. Sergeant.

103
00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:32.029
Password. people?

104
00:09:32.030 --> 00:09:33.197
[Marines] Mojega.

105
00:09:33.198 --> 00:09:35.783
- Friendlies will reply how?
- [Marines] Hump.

106
00:09:35.784 --> 00:09:36.951
[Fleming] You know the mission.

107
00:09:36.952 --> 00:09:38.160
Let's get it done.

108
00:09:38.161 --> 00:09:39.245
Oorah.

109
00:09:39.246 --> 00:09:40.289
Oorah!

110
00:09:46.044 --> 00:09:47.045
Last man.

111
00:09:48.338 --> 00:09:50.340
[tense music playing]

112
00:10:28.962 --> 00:10:30.923
[Thrush] So they'll never invade. huh?

113
00:10:31.507 --> 00:10:34.634
[Beth] I didn't say that. Most of
the people on this fucking base did.

114
00:10:34.635 --> 00:10:36.802
- [intercom dings]
- [Miles] <i>Attention. Happy Valley.</i>

115
00:10:36.803 --> 00:10:39.430
- <i>This is Miles Dale again.</i>
- Like our fearless leader Miles for one.

116
00:10:39.431 --> 00:10:41.599
[Miles] <i>Fighting has spread
throughout the base.</i>

117
00:10:41.600 --> 00:10:43.935
<i>Public places are not safe.</i>

118
00:10:43.936 --> 00:10:47.523
<i>We are still looking for volunteers
who can help fight off this attack.</i>

119
00:10:48.232 --> 00:10:51.651
<i>Reporting centers have been established
at cargo hub four</i>

120
00:10:51.652 --> 00:10:53.320
<i>and the vehicle repair hangar.</i>

121
00:10:53.862 --> 00:10:57.073
<i>If you're not actively engaging
invading forces.</i>

122
00:10:57.074 --> 00:10:58.533
<i>you should shelter in place.</i>

123
00:10:58.534 --> 00:11:00.701
Good to see
so many of us were willing to show up.

124
00:11:00.702 --> 00:11:03.455
- [Miles] <i>Lock your doors. And be careful.</i>
- Everybody...

125
00:11:05.415 --> 00:11:06.416
Gather around.

126
00:11:08.919 --> 00:11:13.506
We've lost contact with old town in the
south. the goo ponds and Agro-2 up north.

127
00:11:13.507 --> 00:11:15.341
Jesus. Ronnie. Already?

128
00:11:15.342 --> 00:11:17.594
Looks like
their ultimate destination is MOCC.

129
00:11:18.262 --> 00:11:20.346
I don't have to tell you what'll happen
to us if they take it.

130
00:11:20.347 --> 00:11:22.139
We were on the surface
when we saw the ships.

131
00:11:22.140 --> 00:11:23.684
I mean. our radios didn't work.

132
00:11:24.351 --> 00:11:25.810
Probably jammed the comm frequencies.

133
00:11:25.811 --> 00:11:27.771
Who here has
military experience besides me?

134
00:11:30.357 --> 00:11:32.650
Good. You're team leaders.

135
00:11:32.651 --> 00:11:34.277
Everybody join one of them.

136
00:11:34.278 --> 00:11:36.279
- Wait. I'm not HVC.
- Media.

137
00:11:36.280 --> 00:11:38.990
- Well. no. not exa...
- Great. Tape everything.

138
00:11:38.991 --> 00:11:41.034
People need
to see what's happening up here.

139
00:11:41.827 --> 00:11:43.202
What about you?

140
00:11:43.203 --> 00:11:45.580
Um. I-I'm in HVC. but I'm a medic.

141
00:11:45.581 --> 00:11:47.291
I only started training last week.

142
00:11:49.459 --> 00:11:50.835
Good.

143
00:11:50.836 --> 00:11:51.879
Here.

144
00:11:52.629 --> 00:11:55.506
I... I don't really know how to use this.
I haven't...

145
00:11:55.507 --> 00:11:57.217
- Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.
- Oh. sorry.

146
00:11:57.885 --> 00:11:59.344
Always assume it's loaded.

147
00:11:59.845 --> 00:12:02.096
Keep your finger off the trigger
until you want to shoot.

148
00:12:02.097 --> 00:12:04.599
Just treat it like a lightsaber.
Don't swing it past anything you don't...

149
00:12:04.600 --> 00:12:06.559
[Marine] Do not move! Drop your weapons.

150
00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:08.769
Place your hands on your heads.
and you will not be harmed.

151
00:12:08.770 --> 00:12:10.396
Everybody down. Take cover. Take cover.

152
00:12:10.397 --> 00:12:11.565
Hold your fire...

153
00:12:17.613 --> 00:12:18.614
[Lily] Oh. God.

154
00:12:20.282 --> 00:12:21.491
[gunshots]

155
00:12:34.254 --> 00:12:36.340
[Marsies shouting]

156
00:12:36.924 --> 00:12:38.217
[Marsie 1] I need more ammo!

157
00:12:43.514 --> 00:12:45.181
[shouts] Wait. Wait!

158
00:12:45.182 --> 00:12:46.308
Shit.

159
00:12:48.185 --> 00:12:49.852
- [Marsie 1] Shoot. shoot!
- [Marsie 2] Go!

160
00:12:49.853 --> 00:12:51.270
Wait. Lily. Lily. Lily!

161
00:12:51.271 --> 00:12:54.732
[Marsie 1] Go. go! Move. move! Go!

162
00:12:54.733 --> 00:12:56.318
[shouting continues]

163
00:12:59.696 --> 00:13:00.697
Get down!

164
00:13:01.448 --> 00:13:03.450
- [canister hissing]
- Move!

165
00:13:06.954 --> 00:13:08.120
We're getting outta here.

166
00:13:08.121 --> 00:13:09.288
When I give you the signal.

167
00:13:09.289 --> 00:13:12.334
you haul ass for the corridor
and then wait for me there. Clear?

168
00:13:16.046 --> 00:13:17.089
Go. go. go!

169
00:13:18.465 --> 00:13:19.549
[Lily] Oh. shit!

170
00:13:19.550 --> 00:13:21.509
All in the clear. Boyd! Haul ass!

171
00:13:21.510 --> 00:13:22.593
[Celia] Clint. move out!

172
00:13:22.594 --> 00:13:23.887
[grunts. exclaims] I'm fine.

173
00:13:26.014 --> 00:13:27.140
[Celia] Cover me!

174
00:13:28.225 --> 00:13:29.517
[Lily] Alex!

175
00:13:29.518 --> 00:13:31.519
Go! Go. I'll catch up.

176
00:13:31.520 --> 00:13:33.564
- No.
- Lily. go!

177
00:13:38.277 --> 00:13:40.696
[lieutenant. in French]
Move! Move! Don't let them escape.

178
00:13:43.657 --> 00:13:44.658
[in English] Shit.

179
00:13:47.494 --> 00:13:48.954
[shouting in French]

180
00:13:57.212 --> 00:13:59.006
[distant gunshots]

181
00:14:03.135 --> 00:14:04.344
[Celia mutters]

182
00:14:08.807 --> 00:14:11.476
So there's another squad of M-6ers
around the next corner.

183
00:14:12.436 --> 00:14:14.437
We have to get past them.

184
00:14:14.438 --> 00:14:15.688
so we have to regroup.

185
00:14:15.689 --> 00:14:18.733
There's more of us that need help. and...
So that's what we're gonna do.

186
00:14:18.734 --> 00:14:19.902
We're gonna help them.

187
00:14:20.402 --> 00:14:23.863
I need you to listen to what I say
when I say it. Clear?

188
00:14:23.864 --> 00:14:25.156
- All right.
- Yeah.

189
00:14:25.157 --> 00:14:26.742
Lily. stay tight.

190
00:14:27.367 --> 00:14:28.911
Kovacic. cover the six.

191
00:14:29.536 --> 00:14:30.537
You're with me.

192
00:14:32.331 --> 00:14:33.789
Ready?

193
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:34.791
Move.

194
00:14:39.713 --> 00:14:42.006
[Oleg] <i>Stuart has synthesizer humming.</i>

195
00:14:42.007 --> 00:14:45.551
<i>Should have it for a return trip
in 24 hours.</i>

196
00:14:45.552 --> 00:14:46.970
[Walt] Oh. shit.

197
00:14:49.389 --> 00:14:51.934
[Oleg] <i>Is there some problem with that?</i>

198
00:14:52.518 --> 00:14:55.561
Negative. Just had the readout
from the analysis program.

199
00:14:55.562 --> 00:14:58.773
The samples from the SEEKER site are
still inconclusive for life.

200
00:14:58.774 --> 00:15:00.566
- No. no. no. no. no.
- Kelly...

201
00:15:00.567 --> 00:15:01.651
Let me see.

202
00:15:01.652 --> 00:15:05.072
[sighs] This has to be
part of a polypeptide chain.

203
00:15:07.324 --> 00:15:09.368
But it has no secondary structure.

204
00:15:10.494 --> 00:15:11.912
Goddamn it.

205
00:15:13.247 --> 00:15:15.832
[Oleg] <i>I guess this means
you're coming back.</i>

206
00:15:33.350 --> 00:15:34.685
Your call. Commander.

207
00:15:45.821 --> 00:15:47.614
Negative. <i>Sojourner.</i>

208
00:15:49.700 --> 00:15:50.993
We're not finished here.

209
00:15:51.577 --> 00:15:54.621
Keep trying to raise MOCC. Away-1 out.

210
00:15:55.497 --> 00:15:56.498
All right.

211
00:15:57.833 --> 00:15:58.916
Okay.

212
00:15:58.917 --> 00:16:03.462
So. SEEKER 4 was sampling
around this rockfall when it conked out.

213
00:16:03.463 --> 00:16:06.632
Seems whatever was in it is
too degraded for a clean sequence.

214
00:16:06.633 --> 00:16:08.801
Yep. [stammers] I'm thinking

215
00:16:08.802 --> 00:16:12.806
that the uncorrupted material could have
come down from above.

216
00:16:14.766 --> 00:16:16.560
Anyone up for a climb?

217
00:16:18.604 --> 00:16:20.272
I thought you'd never ask.

218
00:16:32.701 --> 00:16:33.952
Still warm.

219
00:17:26.964 --> 00:17:28.463
[Haskell] Contact front!

220
00:17:28.464 --> 00:17:29.758
Fuck!

221
00:17:30.384 --> 00:17:32.052
[grunting]

222
00:17:37.474 --> 00:17:38.642
[Haskell] Moving in!

223
00:17:55.742 --> 00:17:58.370
Cedar. check the body and take the door.

224
00:17:59.788 --> 00:18:01.874
Hernandez. do a check here.

225
00:18:20.559 --> 00:18:22.059
Come on. Marines...

226
00:18:22.060 --> 00:18:24.478
Menshikov. you take point.
We still got work to do.

227
00:18:24.479 --> 00:18:25.898
[Menshikov. Hernandez] Yes. Sergeant.

228
00:18:26.607 --> 00:18:28.066
[Marines chattering]

229
00:18:28.901 --> 00:18:30.694
I expected more of a fight.

230
00:18:31.236 --> 00:18:33.446
All these Marsies talking shit.

231
00:18:33.447 --> 00:18:34.615
Come on.

232
00:18:36.617 --> 00:18:38.619
[breathing shakily]

233
00:19:09.191 --> 00:19:11.692
[Ronnie gasping] Help me.

234
00:19:11.693 --> 00:19:13.153
[grunting]

235
00:19:15.364 --> 00:19:16.365
Please.

236
00:19:17.699 --> 00:19:21.369
Oh. Alex. [gasping] Thank God.

237
00:19:21.370 --> 00:19:22.955
Okay. Let me take a look.

238
00:19:26.667 --> 00:19:27.918
Is it bad?

239
00:19:28.544 --> 00:19:30.878
No. No. not horrible.

240
00:19:30.879 --> 00:19:32.296
I'm gonna do what I can. and I'm...

241
00:19:32.297 --> 00:19:34.048
And then I'm gonna get you
to the medbay. Okay?

242
00:19:34.049 --> 00:19:36.717
I'm gonna need you to put pressure on it.
It's gonna hurt a lot.

243
00:19:36.718 --> 00:19:38.261
- [stammering]
- [groaning]

244
00:19:38.262 --> 00:19:41.472
Can you do that for me? Good. Uh. good.

245
00:19:41.473 --> 00:19:43.516
[groans]

246
00:19:43.517 --> 00:19:45.602
Okay. Okay. okay.

247
00:19:49.398 --> 00:19:51.608
Okay. Okay. here we go.

248
00:19:52.734 --> 00:19:54.819
I'm gonna have to put this on you. okay?
I'm gonna need you to lift.

249
00:19:54.820 --> 00:19:58.907
We got this. Okay. ready?
In three. two. one.

250
00:20:04.538 --> 00:20:05.622
[strains]

251
00:20:11.086 --> 00:20:12.920
How you faring up there. Elena?

252
00:20:12.921 --> 00:20:16.299
[Elena] These pitons aren't
quite up for the job in this ice.

253
00:20:16.300 --> 00:20:19.136
Uh. I'm going to start collecting samples.

254
00:20:20.220 --> 00:20:21.513
[grunts]

255
00:20:27.561 --> 00:20:29.479
Uh. hang on.

256
00:20:30.022 --> 00:20:33.900
[sighs] I...
I am seeing something odd up here.

257
00:20:33.901 --> 00:20:35.067
[Kelly] What is it?

258
00:20:35.068 --> 00:20:36.653
[Elena stammers] I'm not sure.

259
00:20:37.321 --> 00:20:40.740
A few meters over.
there's some kind of liquid

260
00:20:40.741 --> 00:20:43.159
that seems to be coming from a fissure.

261
00:20:43.160 --> 00:20:46.538
It looks like it's glowing or something.

262
00:20:47.539 --> 00:20:48.998
- Glowing?
- [Elena] Yeah.

263
00:20:48.999 --> 00:20:51.292
Might just be the reflection of the sky.

264
00:20:51.293 --> 00:20:53.712
I... I'll traverse for a better look.

265
00:20:54.588 --> 00:20:56.381
Can you give me a little bit more slack?

266
00:21:02.054 --> 00:21:03.137
[Elena grunts]

267
00:21:03.138 --> 00:21:04.764
Ah! Shit. shit. shit.

268
00:21:04.765 --> 00:21:06.557
- [Walt] Lena?
- [Elena] Fuck! My leg.

269
00:21:06.558 --> 00:21:08.434
- Lena. are you okay?
- No. No. my...

270
00:21:08.435 --> 00:21:11.270
my axe slipped and it punctured my suit.

271
00:21:11.271 --> 00:21:13.189
Elena. I'm coming up to get you. Hang on.

272
00:21:13.190 --> 00:21:15.859
[Elena screams] It fucking burns!

273
00:21:17.945 --> 00:21:18.946
[Kelly] Okay.

274
00:21:38.715 --> 00:21:39.716
Let's go.

275
00:22:07.578 --> 00:22:08.620
Hold it!

276
00:22:11.248 --> 00:22:12.457
Howdy. Boyd.

277
00:22:13.542 --> 00:22:15.127
Drop the weapon. would you. please?

278
00:22:26.054 --> 00:22:27.556
Hey. Stanislaus.

279
00:22:28.807 --> 00:22:30.434
Got a little present for you.

280
00:22:33.228 --> 00:22:35.021
[Fred] What are we gonna do with them?

281
00:22:35.022 --> 00:22:37.648
Oh. I have a feeling the M-6 is gonna
wanna have a few words

282
00:22:37.649 --> 00:22:39.317
with some of these folks.

283
00:22:39.318 --> 00:22:42.361
Aesop. this is Fenwick-2. Do you read?

284
00:22:42.362 --> 00:22:43.779
[Aesop] <i>Go ahead. Fenwick.</i>

285
00:22:43.780 --> 00:22:49.827
Aesop. we are about 700 meters south
and one level up from Checkpoint Juliet.

286
00:22:49.828 --> 00:22:51.205
Just acquired some new prisoners.

287
00:22:52.581 --> 00:22:55.584
And some possible high-level
intel sources as well.

288
00:22:56.335 --> 00:22:57.753
All right. everybody. listen up.

289
00:22:58.504 --> 00:23:00.506
We're under the Geneva Convention here.

290
00:23:01.298 --> 00:23:02.798
Now. here's what's gonna happen.

291
00:23:02.799 --> 00:23:05.051
We're gonna take you for questioning.

292
00:23:05.052 --> 00:23:09.306
and you're gonna listen
and do exactly what you're told.

293
00:23:10.516 --> 00:23:12.184
And everything should go smoothly.

294
00:23:13.393 --> 00:23:16.230
Sir. this one has a camera.

295
00:23:17.981 --> 00:23:19.816
Ah. the dear leader's daughter.

296
00:23:20.859 --> 00:23:23.444
I'm pr... I'm press. okay?
You can't just take that.

297
00:23:23.445 --> 00:23:28.616
Oh. yeah. That's right. That little. uh.
NNC internship you did where you. um...

298
00:23:28.617 --> 00:23:29.825
Now what was it?

299
00:23:29.826 --> 00:23:33.705
Oh. yeah. leaked the Helios files
which started all this shit.

300
00:23:35.666 --> 00:23:37.209
I don't know what you're talking about.

301
00:23:38.085 --> 00:23:40.671
Yeah. you're about as good
a liar as your old man is.

302
00:23:41.630 --> 00:23:42.965
Keep that camera.

303
00:23:43.632 --> 00:23:45.300
Might be some good intel in there.

304
00:23:46.802 --> 00:23:47.928
All right. let's move it out.

305
00:24:01.316 --> 00:24:02.608
You doing okay?

306
00:24:02.609 --> 00:24:04.193
Fuck off.

307
00:24:04.194 --> 00:24:07.029
Come on. C. You think I like this?

308
00:24:07.030 --> 00:24:08.657
I don't wanna hear shit from you.

309
00:24:11.994 --> 00:24:13.286
- [heart monitor beeping]
- [whimpering]

310
00:24:13.287 --> 00:24:14.746
[bandage tearing]

311
00:24:16.039 --> 00:24:18.959
[Dima] Where did you learn
how to seal a chest wound?

312
00:24:19.877 --> 00:24:21.837
HVC training. My... My first week.

313
00:24:22.629 --> 00:24:24.755
You saved her life.

314
00:24:24.756 --> 00:24:27.258
Don't worry. You're going to be all right.

315
00:24:27.259 --> 00:24:30.386
Fekete. start IV saline.
prep for chest tube.

316
00:24:30.387 --> 00:24:33.055
- Yes. Doctor.
- [nurse] Incoming. More wounded.

317
00:24:33.056 --> 00:24:35.975
- [nurse 2] Where were you?
- Ironworks. Port Four.

318
00:24:35.976 --> 00:24:38.269
Wait. Auggie. Wait. wait. wait.

319
00:24:38.270 --> 00:24:40.022
I'm sorry. you said Port Four?

320
00:24:40.772 --> 00:24:42.565
Did you see Lily there?

321
00:24:42.566 --> 00:24:43.692
No. No.

322
00:24:46.028 --> 00:24:47.112
Fuck.

323
00:24:48.614 --> 00:24:49.698
What is it?

324
00:24:50.490 --> 00:24:53.035
Just... Lily and I. we got separated.

325
00:24:55.204 --> 00:24:57.997
- Dima. I don't know where she is.
- I'm sorry. Alex.

326
00:24:57.998 --> 00:25:01.375
This is the last of the prepacked saline.
and we're out of medgrade sodium chloride.

327
00:25:01.376 --> 00:25:02.503
Fuck.

328
00:25:04.671 --> 00:25:06.548
This is not a field hospital.

329
00:25:07.508 --> 00:25:09.551
We are not provisioned for a war.

330
00:25:10.344 --> 00:25:12.262
They should never have
let it come to this.

331
00:25:13.805 --> 00:25:15.223
Dima. what is it you need?

332
00:25:15.224 --> 00:25:16.350
Everything.

333
00:25:17.267 --> 00:25:22.104
Saline. plasma. gauze. Betadine.
bandages. hemostats.

334
00:25:22.105 --> 00:25:23.606
Wait. Helios has all that stuff.

335
00:25:23.607 --> 00:25:26.275
- I mean. they took most of it from us.
- Exactly.

336
00:25:26.276 --> 00:25:27.819
They've shown us who they really are.

337
00:25:30.030 --> 00:25:31.073
I'll go.

338
00:25:32.574 --> 00:25:34.034
I'll get the stuff.

339
00:25:35.118 --> 00:25:36.411
You sure?

340
00:25:36.912 --> 00:25:38.163
Yes.

341
00:25:39.623 --> 00:25:41.749
Fekete. give Alex
our list of requirements.

342
00:25:41.750 --> 00:25:42.751
Right away.

343
00:25:46.922 --> 00:25:49.508
- Thank you.
- Hey. be careful.

344
00:25:50.175 --> 00:25:52.802
I do not need you
coming back here as a casualty.

345
00:25:52.803 --> 00:25:55.639
Don't worry. I crawled through every vent
and tunnel in this place when I was a kid.

346
00:25:56.265 --> 00:25:57.474
You're still a kid.

347
00:26:06.233 --> 00:26:07.484
[Ronnie strains]

348
00:26:46.440 --> 00:26:49.358
You know. even after
everything that's happened.

349
00:26:49.359 --> 00:26:51.653
I got a lot of respect for your father.

350
00:26:52.905 --> 00:26:54.698
He's a good man. all things considered.

351
00:26:55.574 --> 00:26:57.075
Just trying to protect you.

352
00:26:58.535 --> 00:26:59.912
What are you talking about?

353
00:27:01.914 --> 00:27:03.956
You really haven't figured it out yet.
have you?

354
00:27:03.957 --> 00:27:05.584
- [Spano] Clear. We're clear.
- Huh.

355
00:27:07.461 --> 00:27:08.629
Disappointing.

356
00:27:09.546 --> 00:27:11.548
I thought you wanted to be a journalist.

357
00:27:12.090 --> 00:27:13.091
[Spano] Captain. clear.

358
00:27:14.259 --> 00:27:18.347
Well. why do you think your father
got off scot-free after those riots?

359
00:27:20.307 --> 00:27:23.018
Well. because they tortured him.

360
00:27:28.982 --> 00:27:32.903
He got off because
he ratted out his buddies.

361
00:27:34.988 --> 00:27:35.989
That's bullshit.

362
00:27:37.032 --> 00:27:38.491
Yeah.

363
00:27:38.492 --> 00:27:40.576
It's kind of ironic. isn't it?

364
00:27:40.577 --> 00:27:44.998
The guy who everyone around here
idolizes as some kind of hero...

365
00:27:46.625 --> 00:27:48.501
just a dirty little rat.

366
00:27:48.502 --> 00:27:50.629
You're just a lying piece of shit.

367
00:27:52.297 --> 00:27:53.632
You know what. Lily?

368
00:27:54.883 --> 00:27:57.386
I don't really give a damn
if you believe me or not.

369
00:27:58.470 --> 00:28:04.476
The only thing I care about now
is that you and him pay for what you did.

370
00:28:10.524 --> 00:28:12.860
Aesop. this is Fenwick-2.
Do you read? Over.

371
00:28:18.490 --> 00:28:19.824
[Elena] Oh. fuck.

372
00:28:19.825 --> 00:28:21.284
[panting] It burns.

373
00:28:21.285 --> 00:28:23.035
It's burning.

374
00:28:23.036 --> 00:28:24.912
[Kelly] We're gonna get you down.
okay. Elena?

375
00:28:24.913 --> 00:28:27.124
Walt's on belay.
I'll be guiding you down from up here.

376
00:28:27.708 --> 00:28:29.626
Okay. Let me hook you up.

377
00:28:36.175 --> 00:28:38.009
[Elena breathing heavily]

378
00:28:38.010 --> 00:28:40.469
- I'll be right above you.
- Okay.

379
00:28:40.470 --> 00:28:43.515
- Walt. she's coming down.
- [Walt] Copy.

380
00:28:46.977 --> 00:28:48.812
[Elena] Okay. [straining]

381
00:28:50.647 --> 00:28:52.065
Goddamn it. [grunts]

382
00:28:55.819 --> 00:28:57.778
[Walt] There you go. Take it slow.

383
00:28:57.779 --> 00:28:59.488
[Elena] Walt. Walt. hold... Hold on.

384
00:28:59.489 --> 00:29:01.283
- Okay.
- [Elena panting]

385
00:29:02.034 --> 00:29:03.368
[Walt] Okay. come on now.

386
00:29:04.119 --> 00:29:05.537
[Elena] I think I got it.

387
00:29:06.288 --> 00:29:08.248
[Walt] Good job. You're doing great.

388
00:29:08.790 --> 00:29:12.043
Hold on. Hold on. Slowly. please.

389
00:29:12.044 --> 00:29:13.128
[Walt] Going slowly.

390
00:29:29.478 --> 00:29:33.064
Three. two. one. Breach.

391
00:29:33.065 --> 00:29:34.815
[explosion]

392
00:29:34.816 --> 00:29:37.693
[Marines] Hands on the wall! Freeze!
Against the wall!

393
00:29:37.694 --> 00:29:39.363
[shouting]

394
00:29:40.322 --> 00:29:42.448
Don't shoot! Don't shoot! Don't shoot!

395
00:29:42.449 --> 00:29:44.909
- [Marine] Against the wall!
- [Haskell] Up against the wall.

396
00:29:44.910 --> 00:29:47.037
[Marine 2]
Hands where I can see them. now!

397
00:29:49.039 --> 00:29:50.373
Wait. wait!

398
00:29:50.374 --> 00:29:52.333
I am Governor Leonid Polivanov!

399
00:29:52.334 --> 00:29:53.501
Face the fucking wall!

400
00:29:53.502 --> 00:29:55.712
[Menshikov. in Russian]
We hoped we'd find you. Governor.

401
00:29:56.213 --> 00:29:58.298
[in English]
This is the Governor of Happy Valley.

402
00:30:00.050 --> 00:30:01.634
[Fleming] Bring him over here.

403
00:30:01.635 --> 00:30:03.637
[in Russian]
Thank God this nightmare is over.

404
00:30:05.597 --> 00:30:06.598
[Lenya sighs]

405
00:30:08.642 --> 00:30:10.102
[in English] They held me captive here.

406
00:30:12.646 --> 00:30:13.772
[Fleming] Governor.

407
00:30:14.481 --> 00:30:15.983
Take me to your commanding officer.

408
00:30:16.900 --> 00:30:20.570
I'd like to offer my services
in whatever way I can.

409
00:30:20.571 --> 00:30:22.113
You fucking asshole.

410
00:30:22.114 --> 00:30:23.282
[Marine] Quiet!

411
00:30:24.950 --> 00:30:27.578
Cedar. take the governor to HQ.

412
00:30:28.662 --> 00:30:29.913
Right away. Sergeant.

413
00:30:32.708 --> 00:30:33.876
Right this way. sir.

414
00:30:37.379 --> 00:30:40.757
Haskell. Jarrett.
take the others to prisoner holding.

415
00:30:41.341 --> 00:30:42.466
Let intel sort 'em out.

416
00:30:42.467 --> 00:30:44.136
- Yes. Sergeant.
- [Haskell] Yes. Sergeant.

417
00:30:44.678 --> 00:30:45.762
Behind him.

418
00:30:47.681 --> 00:30:50.099
- Move.
- [Avery] Come on. Move.

419
00:30:50.100 --> 00:30:51.435
Walk. walk. walk!

420
00:31:10.954 --> 00:31:14.875
[Palmer speaking indistinctly]
...we can still make the rendezvous point.

421
00:31:29.014 --> 00:31:30.015
[grunts]

422
00:31:32.226 --> 00:31:33.977
- Keep it tight in the back.
- [Fred] Copy.

423
00:31:37.606 --> 00:31:39.733
Aesop. come in. Over.

424
00:31:44.112 --> 00:31:45.113
[Fred] Clear.

425
00:31:49.368 --> 00:31:51.745
[Palmer] Aesop. Fenwick-2. Do you read?

426
00:31:53.455 --> 00:31:54.539
Clear.

427
00:31:54.540 --> 00:31:56.958
Aesop. Fenwick-2. do you read?

428
00:31:56.959 --> 00:31:58.252
Stop. Stop here.

429
00:32:02.881 --> 00:32:05.175
Huh. No response.

430
00:32:10.931 --> 00:32:14.476
All right. well. Checkpoint Juliet's
100 meters ahead. Let's go.

431
00:32:16.687 --> 00:32:18.689
- [metal creaks]
- [gasps]

432
00:32:21.149 --> 00:32:22.234
What was that?

433
00:32:45.424 --> 00:32:46.925
[softly] Okay. go. Now. Go.

434
00:32:47.676 --> 00:32:48.760
What?

435
00:32:49.303 --> 00:32:51.638
Go. While they're distracted. Go. go. go.

436
00:32:53.557 --> 00:32:56.350
Go. Fast.

437
00:32:56.351 --> 00:32:57.436
Move.

438
00:33:36.266 --> 00:33:37.851
- [Mahdi] Mojega!
- What?

439
00:33:38.393 --> 00:33:40.019
Turn around! On your knees! Now!

440
00:33:40.020 --> 00:33:43.356
- No. no. no. We're on the same side.
- Put your hands down!

441
00:33:43.357 --> 00:33:44.942
[both groups shouting]

442
00:33:46.610 --> 00:33:49.112
- We're MPK!
- I said now!

443
00:33:52.407 --> 00:33:55.243
[gunfire]

444
00:33:55.244 --> 00:33:57.412
- Jesus. What is happening?
- [Celia] Move.

445
00:34:05.921 --> 00:34:07.005
[Mahdi] Fuck.

446
00:34:11.342 --> 00:34:12.511
What'd he say?

447
00:34:13.594 --> 00:34:14.847
[Marine] I don't know.

448
00:34:15.681 --> 00:34:18.265
Shit. these guys are MPKs.

449
00:34:18.266 --> 00:34:19.434
They're on our side.

450
00:34:21.520 --> 00:34:23.437
Leave them. We have to keep moving.

451
00:34:23.438 --> 00:34:25.399
We're already behind the others.

452
00:34:41.748 --> 00:34:42.748
Oh. fuck.

453
00:35:19.703 --> 00:35:20.704
Lily!

454
00:35:34.593 --> 00:35:35.594
[mutters]

455
00:35:58.367 --> 00:36:00.701
- Mojega!
- [sergeant] Mojega! Mojega!

456
00:36:00.702 --> 00:36:03.413
Hump. hump! Goddamn it.

457
00:36:05.541 --> 00:36:07.417
Put your weapons down! We're friendly!

458
00:36:07.918 --> 00:36:09.795
[in French] Nobody shoot! They're M-6.

459
00:36:12.130 --> 00:36:13.423
[in English] Let's move.

460
00:36:14.675 --> 00:36:17.302
[Fleming] Everything is fucked.
We can't reach Command.

461
00:36:21.139 --> 00:36:22.724
Up against this wall. Don't move.

462
00:36:25.602 --> 00:36:26.811
[sergeant] Where are you going?

463
00:36:26.812 --> 00:36:30.106
Taking these prisoners to
the rear holding area. Sergeant.

464
00:36:30.107 --> 00:36:32.984
[sighs] Come on.
you can hump with us back to the rear.

465
00:36:32.985 --> 00:36:35.404
Whoa. whoa. whoa. You're...
You're going the wrong way.

466
00:36:39.449 --> 00:36:43.160
Map says. uh. we should be
moving towards the central elevators.

467
00:36:43.161 --> 00:36:46.582
- That's what we're doing.
- No. No. that's wrong.

468
00:36:49.168 --> 00:36:52.087
I used to live here. okay?
We need to be going that way.

469
00:36:55.841 --> 00:36:57.759
[in French]
This Marsie says our maps are incorrect.

470
00:36:59.178 --> 00:37:00.721
We stick to our briefing.

471
00:37:01.346 --> 00:37:02.805
- [in English] Fall in with us.
- No...

472
00:37:02.806 --> 00:37:05.349
[sergeant] We'll escort the prisoners.
Secure them.

473
00:37:05.350 --> 00:37:06.976
[Marine] Move. Move. Move.

474
00:37:06.977 --> 00:37:07.978
This is fubar.

475
00:37:09.980 --> 00:37:11.190
We're gonna go find our unit.

476
00:37:12.191 --> 00:37:14.984
- Are you disobeying an order?
- Negative. Following one.

477
00:37:14.985 --> 00:37:18.238
We were ordered to hand off the prisoners
to superiors and return to our unit.

478
00:37:19.031 --> 00:37:21.325
And that's exactly
what we're gonna fucking do.

479
00:37:25.037 --> 00:37:26.455
You are a people person. huh?

480
00:37:27.331 --> 00:37:29.791
Come on. I know a shortcut.

481
00:37:30.292 --> 00:37:32.461
We can probably beat our unit
to the rally point.

482
00:37:52.439 --> 00:37:53.856
[chuckles]

483
00:37:53.857 --> 00:37:54.858
Holy shit.

484
00:37:56.443 --> 00:37:57.444
I did that.

485
00:37:57.986 --> 00:37:58.987
Ah.

486
00:38:00.781 --> 00:38:01.865
Right.

487
00:38:25.222 --> 00:38:26.890
[metal crashes in distance]

488
00:38:37.609 --> 00:38:40.361
- We'll plan our sections. Left. right?
- Yeah.

489
00:38:40.362 --> 00:38:42.447
- I take the left. you take the right.
- Yeah.

490
00:39:16.982 --> 00:39:18.525
[metal crashes in distance]

491
00:39:48.430 --> 00:39:50.057
Hey!

492
00:39:50.641 --> 00:39:54.603
[grunting. groans]

493
00:39:55.979 --> 00:39:57.272
[Avery] Haskell?

494
00:39:58.524 --> 00:40:00.691
[Haskell screams. groans]

495
00:40:00.692 --> 00:40:03.570
- [high-pitched ringing]
- [screaming fades out]

496
00:40:07.699 --> 00:40:09.201
[Haskell screaming faintly]

497
00:40:19.253 --> 00:40:20.295
[distorted] Haskell?

498
